A novel and innovative way of issuing community tax certificates and other relevant permits and clearances as a digital certificate is proposed in this patent application. The proposed system involves issuing digital tax certificates to community members through a blockchain-based system, using verifiable credentials, digital wallet as a payment provision, and machine learning.

The system architecture involves a blockchain-based platform that allows community members to register and authenticate themselves through verification of credentials. The digital wallet allows community members to pay the required tax amount through digital currency and store the tax certificate in the digital wallet. The blockchain keeps an immutable record of all interactions between the community members and the system. The machine learning algorithm is used to track the transaction history and calculate the tax amount due by community members. The system also ensures that the tax amount due by each community member is paid in full and keeps a record of the payment made by each community member.

The proposed system can issue digital tax certificates to community members, track the tax amount due and paid by each community member, and maintain a record of the transactions between the community members and the system. The proposed system is novel and non-obvious, and can easily be adapted to other communities and jurisdictions, using similar or different technologies.

